<p>Im using the <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/docs/plugins/embedded-video-player" rel="nofollow">Facebook embedded video player</a> in an modal overlay.</p>  <p>My issue is that when closing down the modal I also want to stop the Facebook video from playing.</p>  <p>There's no real stop, pause, play functions since it embeds itself as an iframe.</p>  <p>Im wondering though if it's possible to clone a working instance of the Facebook video? Then i'd go for an approach of simply removing the current active player entirely from the HTML, so that it stops.</p>  <p>Cloning is somewhat easy, with something like:</p>  <pre><code>//create a temp hidden copy of the video $(".video-fb-container .video-fb-inner.active") .clone() .removeClass("active") .addClass("temp") .appendTo($(".video-fb-container")); </code></pre>  <p>The idea is that I clone (and hide) an instance of the video when opening the modal and then when closing the modal I remove the orignal instance (*hack'ish way to make it stop playing):</p>  <pre><code>//remove active video $(".video-fb-container .video-fb-inner.active").remove();  //swap hidden cloned temp video to be active $(".video-fb-container .video-fb-inner").removeClass("temp").addClass("active"); </code></pre>  <p>The only problem with all of this, it doesn't work. Most likely because the video instantiates uniquely upon page load.</p>  <p>Any ideas how this could possibly work?</p>  <p>The HTML/JS:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div id="fb-root"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;script&gt;(function(d, s, id) {     var js, fjs = d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0];     if (d.getElementById(id)) return;     js = d.createElement(s); js.id = id;     js.src = "//connect.facebook.net/da_DK/sdk.js#xfbml=1&amp;version=v2.4&amp;appId=175301506136607";     fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js, fjs);     }(document, 'script', 'facebook-jssdk'));&lt;/script&gt;  &lt;div id="fb-video-container"&gt;     &lt;div id="fb-video-inner active"&gt;         &lt;div class="fb-video"              data-href="https://www.facebook.com/facebook/videos/10153231379946729/"               data-width="1000"&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>